https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: small Meibomian gland

value.value: decreased size of the meibum-secreting modified lobulated sebaceous glands located at the rim of the eyelids inside the tarsal plate

label.value: Meibomian gland hypoplasia

value.value: マイボーム腺の形成不全

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Meibomian gland hypoplasia

label.value: Meibomian gland cyst

value.value: マイボーム腺嚢腫

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Meibomian gland cyst

value.value: presence of one or more non-malignant fluid-filled cysts in the eyelid area due to non-infectious obstruction or malfunctioning of a Meibomian gland causing extravasation of lipid material in the eyelid soft tissues with focal secondary granulomatous inflammation

label.value: abnormal Meibomian gland physiology

value.value: マイボーム腺の生理異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal Meibomian gland physiology

value.value: any functional anomaly of the meibum-secreting modified lobulated sebaceous glands located at the rim of the eyelids inside the tarsal plate; dysfunctional Meibomian glands may produce an excessive amount of oil, cause dry eyes, or contribute to blepharitis

label.value: Meibomian gland inflammation

value.value: マイボーム腺の炎症

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Meibomian gland inflammation

value.value: local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the meibum-secreting modified lobulated sebaceous glands located at the rim of the eyelids inside the tarsal plate; chronic Meibomian gland inflammation can lead to a lump in the eyelid known as a Meibomian gland cyst (aka chalazion)

label.value: symblepharon

value.value: 眼瞼癒着

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: symblepharon

value.value: partial or complete adhesion of the palpebral conjunctiva of the eyelid to the bulbar conjunctiva of the eyeball

definition.value: Symblepharon is rarely a congenital defect and this condition usually results from trauma such as burns.
